Wabili Workshop Winter Campaign 2024 - The secret lives of lamps

It was so much fun to work with Jon Davis whose photography brought this idea to life and inspired the concept for the campaign. 

Thank you to our favorite model and the world record holder for Wabili Workshop creations, Henry Davis (unrelated Davis’s), whose unwavering support has been the fuel that keeps this endeavor running!

Hi I’m Taylor!
When you’re an unlicensed architect, you call yourself an architectural designer—and that’s what I am. Working professionally as a designer, I design, but I don’t make. And for someone who loves making things, that’s a problem. 

The idea for Wabili Workshop started in December 2023. My mom had some leftover lamp kits from Christmas houses, and I decided to bring them back to New York. I loved the idea of making a lamp because it’s not something most people would think to try on their own—but I wanted to show them that they could.

Hosting is one of my favorite things to do, so I gathered a group of friends and held a lamp-making class in my apartment. It was inspiring to see how uniquely each person approached the open-ended nature of the workshop. Hearing everyone’s excitement about what they created was so rewarding, and that’s when I knew I wanted to do more. 

Since then, I’ve been squeezing in workshops on weekends and after work, growing Wabili Workshop through word of mouth. I never got around to starting an Instagram, but applying to grad school forced me to take pictures of everything—so now I have no excuses. And here I am!

I’m excited you’re here and that you read this far!! People tell me this is long for Instagram lol
